[LLM JUSTIFICATION]
This is a product_issue request seeking guidance on best practices for test variants versus separate tests. The customer is asking for clarification on feature usage and advantages/disadvantages. I used Documents 1, 2, and 4 to provide comprehensive information about test variants: Document 1 explains the variant overview feature; Document 2 describes the simplified variant logic creation workflow; Document 4 provides the core value proposition of variants (delivering correct variant based on candidate input, reducing maintenance overhead, keeping reports clean and role-specific). The response directly addresses the customer's question about when to use variants (for different tech stacks of the same role) versus separate tests, and explains the concrete advantages (streamlined experience, cleaner reporting, reduced maintenance). This can be fully answered with the available corpus and does not require escalation.

