[LLM JUSTIFICATION]
This is a straightforward product_issue involving lost/stolen Visa Traveller's Cheques. The customer has a clear, actionable problem that falls squarely within Visa's travel_support domain. 

I used Document 2 (Report a lost cheque) which states that lost or stolen cheques can be replaced or refunded and directs the customer to call the issuing bank immediately. Document 6 (Have your info ready) provides the specific information the issuer will request. Document 1 (Keep cheques safe) reinforces the importance of reporting to police in case of loss/theft.

The response provides step-by-step guidance grounded in the corpus, including the critical action items (contact issuer, report to police, gather information). The 24-hour refund timeline is cited from Document 6. This is a standard lost/stolen card scenario that can be fully addressed without escalation—the customer has clear next steps and knows what to expect.

